{"title":"Apple’s Keynote, Numbers, and Pages hit version 11 with precise iOS editing","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html","date":1616525173000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><article id=\"post-340345\"><hr><div><div><p><img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"iWork 11\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg 3520w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=1024,683 1024w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=2048,1366 2048w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=1240,826 1240w, https://www.macworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/iwork-11.jpg?resize=150,100 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"></p><p><span></span><span>Apple</span></p></div><div><div id=\"link_wrapped_content\"><p>Apple updated its iWork suite of productivity apps on Tuesday with helpful new features and tweaks that make the apps easier to use. Most notably, the iOS apps now have “Precise editing controls in the Arrange Inspector” to make it easier to fine-tune projects without a Mac. The update to version 11 affects the iPad, iPhone, and Mac versions of Keynote, Numbers, and Pages.&nbsp;The apps jumped to version 10 last March from 8.2.1.</p><h2 id=\"ipad-and-iphone-iwork-updates\">iPad and iPhone iWork updates</h2><p>According to the release notes, the iOS iWork apps all have the following updates:</p><ul><li>Precise editing controls in the Arrange Inspector for adjusting the look and placement of objects</li><li>Onscreen keypads for entering exact values for text size, spacing, table size, and more</li><li>Ability to add or remove objects or table cells from a selection by tapping or dragging across them</li><li>Setting to always open documents in edit mode</li><li>Ability to add phone number links to table cells, text objects, and shapes</li></ul><p>Numbers specifically now has the&nbsp;option to exclude the summary worksheet when exporting your spreadsheet to Microsoft Excel.</p><p>Check out&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/keynote/id361285480&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311gaa&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/keynote/id361285480&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"0\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311gaa\">Keynote</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/numbers/id361304891&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311bga&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/numbers/id361304891&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"1\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311bga\">Numbers</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pages/id361309726&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311fjg&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pages/id361309726&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"2\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311fjg\">Pages</a>&nbsp;on the App Store.</p><h2 id=\"mac-iwork-updates\">Mac iWork updates</h2><p>Here’s what’s new across all the iWork Mac apps, according to the release notes:</p><ul><li>Updated media browser offers enhanced search options and new content categories such as Recents, Portraits and Live Photos</li><li>Ability to add phone number links to table cells, text objects, and shapes</li><li>AppleScript functionality to change a presentation password or open password-protected presentations</li></ul><p>Keynote for Mac specifically has two additional updates:</p><ul><li>View your presenter notes, current slide, and next slide in a separate window while presenting</li><li>Thumbnail images in the build order window make it easier to edit complex sequences</li></ul><p>Check out&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/keynote/id361285480&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311iai&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/keynote/id361285480&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"3\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311iai\">Keynote</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/numbers/id409203825&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311ccj&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/numbers/id409203825&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"4\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311ccj\">Numbers</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pages/id409201541&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0|xid:fr1616525242311gab&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-orig-url=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pages/id409201541&amp;xcust=1-1-340345-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/340345/apples-keynote-numbers-and-pages-hit-version-11-with-precise-ios-editing.html\" data-ml-id=\"5\" data-ml=\"true\" data-xid=\"fr1616525242311gab\">Pages</a>&nbsp;on the Mac App Store.</p></div><p><em>Note: When you purchase something after clicking links in our articles, we may earn a small commission. Read our</em> <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/about/affiliate-link-policy\" target=\"_blank\"><em>affiliate link policy</em></a> <em>for more details.</em></p><ul><a>Related:</a><li><a>Productivity Software</a></li><li><a>iWork</a></li><li><a>Keynote</a></li><li><a>Numbers</a></li><li><a>Pages</a></li></ul><p>Roman has covered technology since the early 1990s. His career started at MacUser, and he's worked for MacAddict, Mac|Life, and TechTV.</p></div></div></article></div>","author"